  <a href="javascript:card_browser(278)">Delving</a> x2<br />
<br />
-.[Shadow Smackdown].- 30<br />
  Orc Butcher x4<br />
  Orc Veteran x4<br />
  Orc Swordsman x4<br />
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(165)">Tower Lieutenant</a> x3<br />
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(869)">Orc Banner</a> x4<br />
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(316)">Gleaming Spires Will Crumble</a> x4<br />
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(1000)">Vile Blade</a> x4<br />
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(159)">Sauron&#39;s Defenses</a> x3<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Note: 4 Axe Strikes and 3 Cleaving Blows also reside in this deck.<br />
<br />
VERY Long Strategy section.<br />
<br><br><br />
First off, the fellowship strategy.  For the dwarves, it&#39;s fairly straightforward: Draw cards, heal as best you can, and move at a reasonable pace.  Try to keep up, somewhat, and see if you can&#39;t get them to go 1-3, 3-5, 6, leaving you sitting at 4 and moving on to five.  You&#39;ll catch them later.  Use your card drawing engine as much as possible: Delving, Tidings, and the Book of Mazarbul should net you a large amount of cards.<br />
<br><br><br />
For your shadow side, your conditions are cheap, and most don&#39;t require you to spot anybody.  For Gleaming Spires, stock up 2 before you play them, so you don&#39;t lose them immediately, and use your Tower Lieutenants (perhaps with a Vile Blade) to back them up.  Don&#39;t play too many minions - let your opponent get confident that your deck sucks, and save the Butchers so as not to reveal your strat (unless he&#39;s looking at your hand already).  At site 7, bounder falls off a cliff, as well as all those nasty elf Allies, and lo and behold, a swarm of cheap and incredibly nasty Orcs ravage the fellowship.<br><br><br />
An orc swordsman armed with a Vile Blade against man or elf is power 15 - otherwise, just 13.  Against men, with 2-4 Gleaming Spires already out, he ranges from 19 to 23 - overwhelming range.  One or two Orc Banners later and he can overwhelm Ranger Boromir.  Cost?  4 shadow.<br><br><br />
Orc Butchers will minimum at base power 10 by site 7.  Against men, 14-18, with a vile blade, 18-22, and the banners add up very quickly.  By the way, he costs 3 (with sword.)<br><br><br />
The Orc Veteran is your Throat Man.  He kills important companions left and right.  Arm him with a blade if you don&#39;t have a swordsman to stick it on, and then whoever he matches up against, discard conditions to drop their power to half of yours.  Keep your Spires if you can, but the Banners must stay, no matter what.  If you have all 3 of Sauron&#39;s Defenses out, you can easily afford to lose 2 of them, if not all 3.  He costs 4 (with sword).<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Matchups:<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Rangers/Elves:<br />
<br><br />
Let them run, and make sure to play out all your fellowship cards and conditions every turn.  Suprise them at site 7 with a handful of Sauron Love.  You should easily win.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Gandalf:<br />
<br><br />
Sleep Caradhras kills this deck.  If it doesn&#39;t show up, then the Orc Veteran is your Gandalf defense - as soon as you have enough conditions out to do it, drop him, a Vile Blade, and all your Gleaming Spires.  Leave him alone.  G-Man will take him and Str -3 him to win the skrimish and destroy the spires.  You proceed to Str -35 the G-Man and kill a focal point of the G-Deck.  You axed your spires and maybe a few Orc Banners, but the appearance of the G-Man means that they&#39;re not playing Rangers anyway, and now his hand will be choked with G-Stuff, and you smile and nod as your dwarves race on to victory.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Hobbits:<br />
<br><br />
There&#39;s nothing for them to stealth from sites 1-5, because you&#39;ll only play maybe 1 minion a turn.  They&#39;ll get hand-screwed and your dwarves will keep up the march on to victory, plus, the Veteran applies much overwhelming at site 7, after the discard of allies.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Dwarves:<br />
<br><br />
Tough.  Fight them every inch of the way - they&#39;ll take wounds from your powerful orcs, and every skirmish you win is an extra +1.  Use the Veteran to overwhelm their power companions when you have a bunch of conditions out, and their fellowship will slowly start to fail.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Final Notes:<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Your fellowship will suffer greatly against Nazgul and Uruk-Hai.  For this reason, you might want to start Fror instead of Gloin, and maybe throw in Companion-Healing-Elrond with Ring to bounce back Black Breaths and Blade Tips.  If you spot either, move very slow and keep the card cycling going, as you&#39;ll need to win with your shadow side.  Good luck!  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=0f944c0585dfb3fafb2b7d724583feda">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24615&PHPSESSID=0f944c0585dfb3fafb2b7d724583feda"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24615&PHPSESSID=0f944c0585dfb3fafb2b7d724583feda" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=0f944c0585dfb3fafb2b7d724583feda">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
